<paragraph blockId="110.[151,1436,1221,1447]" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">
1. Hind femora not swollen or curved (
<figureCitation box="[574,707,1221,1242]" captionStart="FIGURES 221–227" captionStartId="109.[151,263,1767,1790]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1742]" captionTargetId="figure-116@109.[151,1436,193,1746]" captionTargetPageId="109" captionText="FIGURES 221–227. Pyrophanes spp. 221, 222 P. appendiculata (slides, USNM). 223, 224 Luciola venusta type male (MNHN). 225, 226 P. quadrimaculata type female (MNHN). 227 Luciola semilimbata type female (MNHN). 221 male, 222 female abdomens; 223, 225 dorsal; 224 ventral; 226 type labels. Figure legends: 1 anterior projection of aedeagal sheath sternite; 2 basal piece aedeagus; 3 lateral area anterior prolongation of T8; 4 posterior area of aedeagal sheath in region of paraprocts; 5 ventrolateral surface of T8 in spined area; 6 posterolateral area of T8; 7 anterior plates bursa; 8 posterior plates bursa; 9 median oviduct plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5265424" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5265424/files/figure.png" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">Figs 223, 224</figureCitation>
