<subSubSection pageId="110" pageNumber="111" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="110.[151,1440,1485,1761]" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1485,1509]" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Olivier, E." box="[325,490,1485,1509]" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" pagination="333 - 374" refId="ref128538" refString="Olivier, E. (1885) Catalogue des Lampyrides faisant partie des collections du Musee Civique de Genes. Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova, (2 a) 2, 333 - 374." type="journal article" year="1885">Olivier (1885)</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName authority="Motsch." authorityName="Motsch." box="[633,902,1485,1509]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indica">
<emphasis box="[633,800,1485,1509]" italics="true" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">Luciola indica</emphasis>
Motsch.
</taxonomicName>
approached 
<emphasis box="[1052,1192,1485,1509]" italics="true" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">
<taxonomicName box="[1052,1188,1485,1509]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pyrophanes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pyrophanes</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and (1902) formally incorporated it. This species does not belong in 
<taxonomicName box="[730,862,1521,1545]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pyrophanes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[730,862,1521,1545]" italics="true" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">Pyrophanes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and is being addressed (Boontop, Lambkin and Ballantyne in prep.). Certain diagrams of the terminal abdomen of 
<taxonomicName box="[917,1050,1557,1581]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pyrophanes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[917,1050,1557,1581]" italics="true" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">Pyrophanes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are inaccurate e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="Olivier, E." box="[1275,1431,1557,1581]" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" pagination="333 - 374" refId="ref128538" refString="Olivier, E. (1885) Catalogue des Lampyrides faisant partie des collections du Musee Civique de Genes. Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova, (2 a) 2, 333 - 374." type="journal article" year="1885">Olivier (1885</bibRefCitation>
, Plate V, 
<figureCitation box="[259,332,1593,1617]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–17" captionStartId="39.[151,264,1950,1973]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,265,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-85@39.[151,1436,265,1935]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURES 9–17. Australoluciola anthracina type male, Cyclops (MNHN). 9, 10 dorsal (9) and ventral; 11 V6, 7 ventral; 12 pronotum dorsal; 13 type labels; 14 aedeagal sheath ventral; 15-17 aedeagus, dorsal (15), ventral (16) and lateral. These figures share scale lines: 15–17." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5265360" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5265360/files/figure.png" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">Fig.12</figureCitation>
) and 
<bibRefCitation author="Olivier, E." box="[409,567,1593,1617]" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" pagination="1 - 74" refId="ref128760" refString="Olivier, E. (1907) Coleoptera, Lampyridae. Genera Insectorum, 53, 1 - 74 [Luciolinae, 48 - 56]." type="journal article" year="1907">Olivier (1907</bibRefCitation>
Plate 3 
<figureCitation box="[679,767,1593,1617]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–17" captionStartId="39.[151,264,1950,1973]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,265,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-85@39.[151,1436,265,1935]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURES 9–17. Australoluciola anthracina type male, Cyclops (MNHN). 9, 10 dorsal (9) and ventral; 11 V6, 7 ventral; 12 pronotum dorsal; 13 type labels; 14 aedeagal sheath ventral; 15-17 aedeagus, dorsal (15), ventral (16) and lateral. These figures share scale lines: 15–17." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5265360" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5265360/files/figure.png" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
) are inaccurate representations of the terminal ventrite; 
<bibRefCitation author="McDermott, F. A." box="[151,385,1629,1653]" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" pagination="1 - 72" refId="ref127702" refString="McDermott, F. A. (1964) The taxonomy of the Lampyridae. Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 90, 1 - 72." type="journal article" year="1964">McDermott’s (1964)</bibRefCitation>
brief redescription of 
<taxonomicName box="[650,782,1629,1653]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pyrophanes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[650,782,1629,1653]" italics="true" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">Pyrophanes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was probably influenced by the atypical abdomen of 
<taxonomicName authority="McLean" authorityName="McLean" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Photinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macdermotti">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">P. macdermotti</emphasis>
McLean
</taxonomicName>
which he is known to have examined at this time and he misinterpreted various aspects. Ballantyne in 
<bibRefCitation author="Calder, A. A." box="[314,474,1701,1725]" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" refId="ref123793" refString="Calder, A. A. (1998) Coleoptera: Elateroidea In Wells, A. (ed.) Zoological Catalogue of Australia, 29.6 (CSIRO Publishing Melbourne)." type="book" year="1998">Calder (1998)</bibRefCitation>
synonymised 
<taxonomicName authority="Lea" authorityName="Lea" authorityYear="1921" box="[642,915,1701,1725]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="complicata">
<emphasis box="[642,862,1701,1725]" italics="true" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">Luciola complicata</emphasis>
Lea
</taxonomicName>
from far north 
<collectingRegion box="[1101,1233,1701,1725]" country="Australia" name="Queensland" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">Queensland</collectingRegion>
with 
<taxonomicName authority="Olivier." authorityName="Olivier." class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pyrophanes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beccarii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">Pyrophanes beccarii</emphasis>
Olivier.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
